Last Usage Date = 
MAXX(
    FILTER(
        Metrics,
        Metrics[Metric Type] = "Used Licenses"
    ),
    Metrics[Date]
)







If we switch to a column instead of a measure, it will respect product-level row context and give the right result:

    Go to the Metrics table.

    Create a new column, not a measure:

Latest Usage Date Per Product = 
CALCULATE(
    MAX(Metrics[Date]),
    FILTER(
        Metrics,
        Metrics[Metric Type] = "Used Licenses"
            && Metrics[Product] = EARLIER(Metrics[Product])
    )
)
